(137, 137, 'Mis-a-jour des donnees', '<p>cette article existe en anglais.</p>\n<p>In the new version of the site articles are managed separately from the rest of the data.</p>\n<h1><strong>To edit articles</strong></h1>\n<ul>\n<li>from the user screens - click on the edit icon but ONLY edit the French versions of a document.¬† to edit the translation in English you have to use JOOMFISH see later. ;</li>\n<li>from the Administrator¬† - go to Content&gt;Articles select the article and edit it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>¬†</p>\n<p>For all other updates you have to log in as administrator.</p>\n<h1><strong>To upload images </strong></h1>\n<ol>\n<li>go to Site&gt;Gestion des Medias</li>\n<li>all images we use are to be stored under stories&gt;fflsas&gt;newimages</li>\n<li>use the upload button to upload an image into the site.</li>\n<li>this image can then be included in any article.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1><strong>To edit images, people and events</strong></h1>\n<p>For the rest of the data you will have to use the com_FFLSAS_admin component.</p>\n<p>Select¬† Composants&gt;FFLSAS_admin.</p>\n<p>You then have three Choices¬†¬† Person, Event , Image</p>\n<p>¬†</p>\n<h2 style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>To edit People select Person</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Here you can create edit and delete people the screens are simillar to the old ones and behave in the same way.</p>\n<h2 style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>To create edit events select Event</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Here you can create edit and delete events the screens are simillar to  the old ones and behave in the same way.</p>\n<h2 style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>To edit images select Image</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Here you can add new images from \"newimage\" directory¬† set their access rights and add a label and description.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><strong>access rights </strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">\n<li