(738, 'event', '160', 'comment', 'FR', '<p align=justify>Depuis pr√®s d\'un an, le Lt Marienne entra√Æne ses hommes pour ce moment tant attendu de pouvoir, le premier, fouler le sol de France en lib√©rateur.\r\n<br>Il est 00h30 le 6 juin 1944 et √†¬† travers le trou du Stirling, le dispatcher regarde d√©filer la campagne bretonne. La lumi√®re est au rouge, \"Action - Station\".\r\n<br>Les hommes du stick Marienne se l√®vent et accrochent la sangle de leur parachute √†¬† la static line qui traverse l\'avion.\r\n<br>Soudain, le pilote d√©couvre les rep√®res et la proximit√© de la DZ. La lumi√®re passe au vert. \"Go!\"', 'David Portier', '2006-10-16 12:35:48'),
(739, 'event', '330', 'comment', 'FR', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Le groupe du lieutenant Marienne touche terre √† 00h45 √†  deux kilom√®tres de l\'endroit pr√©vu, dans les landes √†  l\'est du hameau de Halliguen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sans le savoir, les parachutistes fran√ßais sont tomb√©s √†  huit cents m√®tres du Moulin de la Gr√©e √†  Plumelec, transform√© en poste d\'observation par les Allemands.<br />Aussit√¥t, l\'alerte est donn√©e et un d√©tachement de G√©orgiens se lance √†  la recherche des SAS. <br /><br />Tandis qu\'une partie du stick est √†  la recherche de la malle en osier du capitaine Andr√© Hunter-Hue alias Fernand, agent du SOE parachut√© avec les SAS, le caporal Bou√©tard et l\'√©quipe radio sont encercl√©s. Rapidement, Emile Bou√©tard est bless√© et achev√© par l\'ennemi alors que Jordan, Etrich et Sauv√© sont faits prisonniers.<br /><br />Au bruit des combats, le stick se disperse. Tandis que le lieutenant Marienne, Louis et Krysik d√©crochent vers le sud, traversent La Claie et rejoignent la Petite-M√©tairie, le Sgt/C Raufast et le capitaine Andr√© partent vers Saint-Jean-Br√©velay.</p>', 'David Portier', '2012-10-13 11:14:18'),
(740, 'event', '162', 'comment', 'EN', ' A standard 2nd SAS mission dropped to the SE of Vtre to collect information on enmey movements and to harrass them.', 'David Portier', '2006-05-22 11:51:11'),
(741, 'event', '163', 'comment', 'EN', ' The stick, led by Captain Lee 2SAS was parachuted to the South of Paris in July with the objective of capturing Rommel.', 'David Portier', '2006-03-17 14:49:53'),
(742, 'event', '164', 'comment', 'EN', '<p align=justify>Deplante was charged by Bourgoin to set up a northern base to replace the lost Samwest base.  The was to receive redistribute and then co-ordinate the work of SAS and resistance coming from the overrun Dingson base and the Duault(Samwest) bases.', 'David Portier', '2006-09-14 14:08:34'),
(743, 'event', '165', 'comment', 'EN', 'As the liberating forces gained a substantial foothold in Normandy and the enemy forces in Britany were being defeated, the SAS were being required to operate further east.  To supply adequate transport a major delivery of jeeps was made, by parachute and by gliders under the noses of the occupation forces in Vannes.  Betbeze. Paoli, Itturia and the reserve 4SAS arrived with the jeeps near Mallachappe.  There was a certain impatiance in these forces having missed the first two months of the liberation, however the enemy were far from defeated and much of France was still occupied so there was still work to be done. ', 'david', '2009-06-16 18:24:21'),
(744, 'event', '166', 'comment', 'EN', ' Harassing the enemy facilitating the progress of alied forces arriving from the south. ', '*', '2003-01-01 00:00:00'),
(745, 'event', '167', 'comment', 'EN', ' Paracuted South of Lamure on 18/8/1944', '*', '2003-01-01 00:00:00'),
(746, 'event', '168', 'comment', 'EN', '', 'David Portier', '2012-05-18 13:54:48');
